This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it presents an algorithm for training deep neural networks. The use of quadratic functions in the network architecture suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses practical implementations and experimental results, which are common in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The mention of kernel learning suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the use of a layer-by-layer algorithm for training the network may also make it relevant to the cs.SD (Software Engineering) sub-category.
